ocumentation in ICS."},{"title":"Honeywell Security Bulletin Template","url":" https://www.honeywellprocess.com/library/support/notifications/Pages/default.aspx","description":"Example of structured security update documentation."}]},{"id":"KA3","title":"Version Impact Analysis","description":"Analyzing how patches affect different versions helps prevent unintended consequences in complex ICS environments with multiple interdependent components.","related_links":[{"title":"ABB Patch Impact Assessment","url":"https://new.abb.com/control-systems/cyber-security/security-advisories","description":"ABB's methodology for version-specific patch impact analysis."},{"title":"ICS-CERT Vulnerability Coordination","url":"https://www.cisa.gov/uscert/ics/advisories","description":"Case studies of version-specific vulnerability management."}]},{"id":"KA4","title":"Legacy Version Support","description":"Developing strategies for maintaining security in older versions that may no longer receive updates is crucial for long-lifecycle ICS assets.","related_links":[{"title":"Rockwell Legacy Product Security","url":"https://www.rockwellautomation.com/en-us/support/security-advisories.html","description":"Approaches for securing obsolete versions of ICS components."},{"title":"NIST SP 800-82 Rev3","url":"https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/SpecialPublications/NIST.SP.800-82r3.pdf","description":"Guidance on securing legacy industrial control systems."}]}],"name":"Security update documentation","description":"A process shall be employed to ensure that documentation about product security updates is made available to product users that includes but is not limited to: a) the product version number(s) to which the security patch applies;","details":{"risk_assessment_and_threat_modeling":{"why":"To ensure security updates address relevant vulnerabilities and threats.","methodologies":[{"name":"STRIDE","description":"Used to identify potential threats (Spoofing, Tampering, Repudiation, Informatio